data.description: Welcome to this enchanting Victorian-style home, a timeless beauty built in 1910 nestled in the serene town of Lansford, North Dakota. Boasting a steel roof that exudes durability and character, this residence sits gracefully on two and a half expansive lots, offering ample space for all your desires. As you approach, a covered front porch invites you to step into a world of craftsmanship and charm. The cozy family room warmly welcomes you upon entry, setting the tone for the comfort and elegance that this home offers. To the right, a hardwood floor living room extends seamlessly into a spacious dining room with French doors that beckon you to the backyard. The living room is a haven of natural light, thanks to its abundant windows, creating a delightful atmosphere for everyday living. The dining room, an ideal space for entertaining family and friends, promises memorable home-cooked meals and joyous holiday gatherings. It's a room where cherished memories are sure to be made. The kitchen, adorned with hickory cabinets, is a haven for any aspiring chef. Its perfect size allows you to whip up culinary delights while enjoying the home's warmth and character. Nestled between the family room and the kitchen, a convenient half bath with laundry facilities adds to the home's functionality. Venturing upstairs, the master bedroom awaits with its generous proportions, complete with a relaxing jacuzzi tub and a lofted closet. The master bedroom is a true retreat, and it holds a delightful secret – a door that opens onto a spacious deck. This expansive deck is the perfect spot to while away summer afternoons, immersing yourself in the soothing sounds of chirping birds and the gentle rustling of leaves. Two additional bedrooms offer cozy retreats, and the full bathroom boasts charming tile accents. This home's upper level is a tranquil sanctuary for rest and relaxation. Last but not least, the basement provides abundant storage space, ensuring that you have room for all your belongings. This Victorian-style home is a true gem, with its rich history, craftsmanship, and a layout designed for modern living. Don't miss the opportunity to make it your own and experience the comfort and beauty it offers. Welcome to a place where the past and present gracefully merge, creating a timeless haven for you and your loved ones. One of the key advantages of this location is its proximity to the Minot Air Force Base, making it an ideal residence for military personnel and their families. Additionally, the city of Minot, with its amenities, shopping, dining, and cultural attractions, is just a short drive away.
